25/06/2008
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- A BiH court reached a verdict in the embezzlement case against the forestry company Srpske Sume on Tuesday (June 24th), sentencing former Republika Srpska Prime Minister Mladen Ivanic to 18 months in prison.
The court convicted Ivanic, leader of the Party of Democratic Progress, of negligence and mismanagement while serving as prime minister.
It acquitted him of abuse-of-office charges and conspiracy to commit crime and bribery.
(Blic, RTRS, SRNA, Dnevni Avaz - 24/06/08)
